The paper is about named entity recognition (NER) using convolutional neural networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also proposes a new network architecture, which involves modeling relations between words and using them as gates to fuse local context features into global ones. This suggests that the paper may also belong to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which cover topics related to neural networks and deep learning. Additionally, the paper may belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which covers topics related to neural networks and their applications. Finally, since the proposed network involves convolutional layers, the paper may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision), which covers topics related to image and video processing.
